In this article, President Obama discusses his trip to Latin America and emphasizes the importance of strengthening economic partnerships with the region to create more jobs in the United States. He highlights the rapid economic growth in Latin America and the increasing demand for goods and services in the region. The President expresses his goal of opening more global markets for American companies to do business and hire more people. He mentions that every $1 billion of goods and services exported supports over 5,000 jobs in the US, and he aims to double exports by 2014. President Obama provides examples of American companies that have benefited from exporting to Brazil and mentions his meetings with business leaders to deepen economic ties. He also mentions visiting Chile and El Salvador, countries with growing economies and increasing demand for American goods. The President emphasizes the importance of the partnership with Latin America in the global economy and how it benefits both the people of Latin America and the American people.